node.text:
To celebrate #worldbreastfeedingweek, (re)sharing @alicebleiter's honest and powerful story. "That’s what we should judge: Not that I couldn’t make enough milk, but that I felt guilty about it." See the rest of her story at the link in bio.

There is no hierarchy for how parents should feed their babies. Fed is best. Parents taking care of themselves... also best. 💛 

#worldbreastfeedingweek2021

node.text:
"Our children’s lives — the BASICS like their health, the ability to attend in-person school and see friends and family — are being sacrificed at the hands of people who won’t participate in public health measures. Kids, who have so little control over their lives, are taking on so much of the burden."

For whomever else needs to read this today 🙋‍♀️LINK IN BIO for @abbyras' post about how kids (not to mention parents, teachers, essential workers and, most of all, healthcare workers) are sacrificing for the willfully unvaxxed.
